The Jesuites intrigues with the private instructions of that society to their emissaries : the first, translated out of a book privately printed at Paris : the second, lately found in manuscript in a Jesuites closet, after his death : both sent with a letter from a gentleman at Paris to his friend in London. Gentleman at Paris. Compton, Henry, 1632-1713.
[14], 62 p.
Printed for Benjamin Tooke ..., London : 1669.
Original title for "The Jesuites intrigues" undetermined. Second part of work is a translation of: Monita Secreta Societatis Jesu. Translated by Henry Compton. Cf. DNB. Reproduction of original in Cambridge University Library.
